19
00:00:18,481 --> 00:00:19,524
<i>Kidnapped!</i>

20
00:00:19,607 --> 00:00:22,318
<i>During a Separatist invasion
of the planet Kiros,</i>

21
00:00:22,443 --> 00:00:26,489
<i>thousands of peaceful colonists
were abducted by Zygerrian slavers.</i>

22
00:00:27,323 --> 00:00:31,369
<i>Determined to find the missing colonists,
the Jedi travel to Zygerria,</i>

23
00:00:31,494 --> 00:00:34,830
<i>home to the galaxy's
most notorious slave empire.</i>

24
00:00:47,802 --> 00:00:50,638
It looks like Zygerria
is a popular place these days.

25
00:00:50,721 --> 00:00:51,764
Hmm.

26
00:00:51,806 --> 00:00:55,851
Whatever is happening
is attracting plenty of high class scum.

27
00:01:20,835 --> 00:01:24,171
Let's just hope the information our spies
gave us about the Queen is accurate.

28
00:01:24,505 --> 00:01:26,173
Remember, I'll keep her occupied

29
00:01:26,257 --> 00:01:28,676
while you locate
the missing people of Kiros.

30
00:01:28,759 --> 00:01:32,054
How do you plan
on keeping the Queen occupied?

31
00:01:33,347 --> 00:01:37,852
-With my magnetic charm, of course.
-Oh, yes, of course.

32
00:01:38,769 --> 00:01:40,688
Hold on to this, will you, buddy?

33
00:01:56,454 --> 00:01:59,957
Remind me why I'm the one
playing the part of the slave?

34
00:02:00,041 --> 00:02:02,877
I tried it once, I wasn't any good at it.

35
00:02:02,918 --> 00:02:06,631
Besides, the role of master
comes easily to me.

36
00:02:06,881 --> 00:02:10,301
Really? Well, this time
try to be convincing at it.

37
00:02:28,861 --> 00:02:29,904
Ugh!

38
00:02:29,945 --> 00:02:33,783
How can a civilization this advanced
still practice slavery?

39
00:02:33,908 --> 00:02:37,203
It makes them wealthy and powerful
at the expense of others.

40
00:02:37,244 --> 00:02:42,041
Before the Hutts bought my mother,
she was sold in a market just like this.

41
00:02:53,552 --> 00:02:55,930
Get up, you useless skug.

42
00:02:56,305 --> 00:02:59,767
Master, the bonds, they are too heavy.

43
00:03:01,102 --> 00:03:02,937
Tell it to my whip.

44
00:03:06,399 --> 00:03:08,484
You don't want to do that.

45
00:03:11,112 --> 00:03:12,780
You dare touch me!

46
00:03:12,905 --> 00:03:16,784
Excuse my slave, friend.
She is freshly caught.

47
00:03:17,535 --> 00:03:20,079
Hmm. What have we here?

48
00:03:20,121 --> 00:03:24,083
You wear Zygerrian armor,
but you are not one of us.

49
00:03:24,917 --> 00:03:26,293
Who are you?

50
00:03:26,627 --> 00:03:28,671
I've come for an audience with the Queen.

51
00:03:29,130 --> 00:03:31,173
Then you have an invitation?

52
00:03:31,298 --> 00:03:34,468
We can't just let anyone in
to speak with Her Majesty.

53
00:03:34,844 --> 00:03:40,182
No invitation, but I do bring news,
news the Queen will be eager to hear.

54
00:03:40,850 --> 00:03:44,311
I doubt that,
you're nothing more than a brigand.

55
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:48,107
I wouldn't say that,
especially when the Queen learns

56
00:03:48,149 --> 00:03:52,153
you prevented her from hearing
the news about Bruno Denturri.

57
00:03:55,322 --> 00:03:57,992
<i>Halt! Cease all hostilities.</i>

58
00:03:58,617 --> 00:04:02,496
<i>This man is to be escorted to the palace,
by order of the Queen.</i>

59
00:04:33,152 --> 00:04:37,031
Make certain all preparations
are complete for this evening.

60
00:04:42,036 --> 00:04:44,038
And fetch refreshments.

61
00:04:44,830 --> 00:04:48,584
My Queen, I present Lars Quell.

62
00:04:49,001 --> 00:04:50,044
Hmm.

63
00:04:50,085 --> 00:04:54,548
So, you are the man who claims
to be acquainted with Bruno Denturri?

64
00:04:55,007 --> 00:04:56,550
Yes, Your Highness.

65
00:04:56,675 --> 00:05:00,763
However, when I spoke with him
he failed to describe your beauty.

66
00:05:03,057 --> 00:05:04,308
Really?

67
00:05:04,391 --> 00:05:07,770
And did Bruno
speak of my intense hatred of him?

68
00:05:08,187 --> 00:05:10,898
Or did that escape his memory as well?

69
00:05:12,608 --> 00:05:15,236
He needed not speak of it, Your Majesty.

70
00:05:15,277 --> 00:05:20,741
In fact, Bruno Denturri
will not be speaking ever again.

71
00:05:21,951 --> 00:05:23,369
What do you mean?

72
00:05:23,744 --> 00:05:27,039
Bruno Denturri is dead by my hand.

73
00:05:27,081 --> 00:05:31,085
Here is a slave from his palace,
compensation for my efforts.

74
00:05:33,295 --> 00:05:35,089
Unhand me, brigand!

75
00:05:39,051 --> 00:05:41,220
You impress me, Lars Quell.

76
00:05:42,721 --> 00:05:44,932
She is quite a prize.

77
00:05:45,057 --> 00:05:48,227
And to have defeated
Bruno Denturri in combat,

78
00:05:50,312 --> 00:05:52,731
you must be quite the warrior.

79
00:05:53,274 --> 00:05:54,358
Hmm.

80
00:05:54,692 --> 00:05:55,776
Mmm-hmm.

81
00:05:55,818 --> 00:05:58,445
The slave is certainly of fine stock,

82
00:05:58,571 --> 00:06:02,116
Bruno always knew
how to choose a beautiful female.

83
00:06:02,157 --> 00:06:04,952
Don't you dare touch me!

84
00:06:08,747 --> 00:06:10,666
Though she will have to be processed.

85
00:06:11,458 --> 00:06:14,253
Her demeanor leaves much to be desired.

86
00:06:14,837 --> 00:06:16,630
What is your price for her?

87
00:06:16,922 --> 00:06:20,301
With respect,
how can I price the beauty of this slave,

88
00:06:20,467 --> 00:06:23,178
when I look upon
the magnificence of Your Highness,

89
00:06:23,304 --> 00:06:27,099
whose beauty would make
the brightest star seem dull by comparison.

90
00:06:28,267 --> 00:06:30,311
Lars Quell, you flatter me.

91
00:06:30,978 --> 00:06:33,480
No, Your Majesty, however...

92
00:06:39,153 --> 00:06:41,447
Lars, stop it. Stop it!

93
00:06:42,489 --> 00:06:44,158
You are a bold one, aren't you?

94
00:06:44,825 --> 00:06:47,369
My reputation precedes me then.

95
00:06:47,494 --> 00:06:50,873
Perhaps we can find a way
to put a price on your slave.

96
00:06:50,998 --> 00:06:52,833
Come, walk with me.

97
00:07:29,995 --> 00:07:32,081
Sir, take a look at this.

98
00:07:38,045 --> 00:07:40,714
Stand watch, I'll take a closer look.

99
00:07:45,010 --> 00:07:46,345
Governor Roshti?

100
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:49,723
No! No!

101
00:07:50,599 --> 00:07:54,395
Governor, I'm a friend, a Jedi, here to help.

102
00:07:55,437 --> 00:07:57,940
-Where are your people?
-They're...

103
00:08:10,035 --> 00:08:12,413
-Sir, did you find out where the others are?
-Not yet.

104
00:08:13,080 --> 00:08:14,623
We've got to get him out of here.

105
00:08:25,926 --> 00:08:28,804
You there,
what are you doing with that slave?

106
00:09:00,919 --> 00:09:03,964
Slavery is the natural order of things.

107
00:09:04,006 --> 00:09:05,591
The weak deserve nothing more

108
00:09:05,632 --> 00:09:09,470
than to kneel before the strong,
bound to our service.

109
00:09:09,511 --> 00:09:14,475
I will need men with your talents
to spread our ways across the galaxy.

110
00:09:20,647 --> 00:09:22,733
Let me go!

111
00:09:23,650 --> 00:09:28,614
You dare raise a hand against your master.
Clearly you require further processing.

112
00:09:29,114 --> 00:09:32,326
No! I won't go back there.

113
00:09:33,744 --> 00:09:35,120
Wait! Stop!

114
00:09:41,627 --> 00:09:43,003
Such a waste.

115
00:09:43,128 --> 00:09:46,507
But perhaps she was more trouble
than she's worth.

116
00:09:46,590 --> 00:09:50,677
But you, Lars,
you are proving quite resourceful.

117
00:09:52,346 --> 00:09:56,350
Very well, I will pay your price
for this slave girl.

118
00:09:57,017 --> 00:10:00,854
It seems
I am in need of a new servant.

119
00:10:03,690 --> 00:10:06,443
She is my gift to you, Your Highness.

120
00:10:07,694 --> 00:10:12,032
You are a man of many surprises.
It pleases me.

121
00:10:12,950 --> 00:10:15,619
I wish you to be my guest
at the slave auction,

122
00:10:15,702 --> 00:10:17,704
and to sit at my side.

123
00:10:30,717 --> 00:10:31,718
Well...

124
00:10:34,012 --> 00:10:38,642
-Who is he?
-He hasn't talked, but I'll loosen his tongue.

125
00:10:40,686 --> 00:10:44,398
Why would a slaver
try to rescue a slave from the palace?

126
00:10:45,732 --> 00:10:47,234
It's suicide.

127
00:10:50,737 --> 00:10:55,534
Wait. I know you from the hologram.

128
00:10:57,995 --> 00:10:59,997
I never forget a Jedi.

129
00:11:09,256 --> 00:11:14,803
Your Highness, Zygerrians,
and guests from a thousand worlds,

130
00:11:14,928 --> 00:11:16,221
our auction begins

131
00:11:16,263 --> 00:11:22,311
with slaves of unmatched quality
and impossible quantity.

132
00:11:22,978 --> 00:11:27,608
I give you Togruta from the Kiros System!

133
00:11:32,196 --> 00:11:34,114
Oh, no.

134
00:11:34,781 --> 00:11:38,285
This handsome sample
represents a lot of numbering,

135
00:11:38,327 --> 00:11:42,164
no less than 50,000 beings.

136
00:11:43,081 --> 00:11:45,125
Note the compliance.

137
00:11:45,792 --> 00:11:48,420
Virtually untrained in combat.

138
00:11:48,462 --> 00:11:51,590
There will be no rebellion
from these slaves.

139
00:11:51,632 --> 00:11:55,802
So where do you keep 50,000 slaves,
like the people of Kiros?

140
00:11:59,306 --> 00:12:01,975
Your Majesty, I have urgent news.

141
00:12:08,649 --> 00:12:10,984
All will be revealed in time.

142
00:12:14,529 --> 00:12:18,867
Before we begin the auction,
I would welcome a most special guest,

143
00:12:19,701 --> 00:12:24,164
Obi-Wan Kenobi, Jedi knight!

144
00:12:25,499 --> 00:12:29,336
Down with the Jedi !
The Jedi are not so tough.

145
00:12:29,962 --> 00:12:34,132
My friends, my good friends,
do not fear the Jedi.

146
00:12:34,508 --> 00:12:38,178
They are no different from others
we have forced into submission,

147
00:12:38,220 --> 00:12:42,557
for they have forsaken their ideals
to serve a corrupt Senate.

148
00:12:42,683 --> 00:12:45,727
Every Jedi
has become a slave to the Republic.

149
00:12:46,687 --> 00:12:50,899
The Jedi Order is weak,
and we will help break it.

150
00:12:53,527 --> 00:12:55,696
Teach the Jedi his place.

151
00:13:17,968 --> 00:13:23,807
Whip the Jedi ! Whip the Jedi !
Whip the Jedi ! Whip the Jedi!

152
00:13:24,725 --> 00:13:28,395
Looks like
I have to rescue you again, old man.

153
00:13:28,478 --> 00:13:30,897
I knew you'd have a backup plan.

154
00:13:35,861 --> 00:13:40,657
Prove to me you are a slaver.
Swing that whip, or die beside him.

155
00:13:43,160 --> 00:13:45,412
Those are some lousy options.

156
00:13:55,505 --> 00:13:58,050
You leave me no choice, Highness.

157
00:14:12,272 --> 00:14:13,899
Guards, subdue them!

158
00:14:33,877 --> 00:14:35,087
Ahsoka, the Queen!

159
00:14:36,463 --> 00:14:39,299
Looks like your slave empire
is finished, again.

160
00:14:39,633 --> 00:14:42,928
Get that thing out of my face,
you little skug!

161
00:15:20,340 --> 00:15:22,175
Such determination.

162
00:15:44,322 --> 00:15:47,826
You destroyed my auction
and frightened my customers.

163
00:15:49,411 --> 00:15:52,706
Count Dooku and half my kingdom
are demanding your death.

164
00:15:54,833 --> 00:15:59,504
You should have listened to them.
My friends, where are they?

165
00:16:02,215 --> 00:16:06,428
Continue to misbehave and they die.

166
00:16:13,852 --> 00:16:18,398
A most curious Jedi who cares more
about his friends than his own mission.

167
00:16:18,523 --> 00:16:20,400
Hero. General.

168
00:16:22,235 --> 00:16:24,070
And now my servant.

169
00:16:28,033 --> 00:16:29,910
I will not serve you.

170
00:16:32,245 --> 00:16:34,915
Your heart is not in your words.

171
00:16:35,040 --> 00:16:38,710
You will stand beside me,
a testament to my power.

172
00:16:39,419 --> 00:16:42,923
Here, my bodyguard will need a weapon.

173
00:16:44,132 --> 00:16:48,762
And you need not worry about your friends,
they will be quite safe.

174
00:17:08,281 --> 00:17:11,159
The Queen has promised
once the other Jedi is tamed,

175
00:17:11,743 --> 00:17:14,454
you will be mine, little skug.

176
00:17:17,040 --> 00:17:18,124
Whoa!

177
00:17:23,964 --> 00:17:26,174
You better hope that doesn't happen.

178
00:18:14,055 --> 00:18:16,516
My people, we have found them.

179
00:18:17,350 --> 00:18:18,852
Keep moving, skug.

180
00:18:24,482 --> 00:18:27,861
General Kenobi, you are the first Jedi

181
00:18:27,902 --> 00:18:31,698
I have entertained
at our educational center.

182
00:18:32,532 --> 00:18:36,161
Few possess a Jedi's resolve,

183
00:18:36,202 --> 00:18:39,873
and it is strength of will
that is my greatest enemy.

184
00:18:54,012 --> 00:18:56,890
Now that I have your attention, Jedi,

185
00:18:57,015 --> 00:19:02,687
be aware that it will not be you who suffers
should you defy me.

186
00:19:12,405 --> 00:19:15,075
You were once a slave, weren't you?

187
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,577
What makes you think I was a slave?

188
00:19:17,744 --> 00:19:20,580
The noble selflessness in your eyes.

189
00:19:20,705 --> 00:19:24,626
Your commitment to the service
of something greater than yourself.

190
00:19:24,751 --> 00:19:29,047
Your Jedi, the grand Republic,
even your friends.

191
00:19:29,798 --> 00:19:31,966
I don't see commitment as slavery.

192
00:19:32,092 --> 00:19:35,220
Oh, it is when it comes
at the cost of yourself.

193
00:19:36,596 --> 00:19:38,431
What you could be!

194
00:19:38,473 --> 00:19:43,436
With you willingly beside me,
there is nothing we could not accomplish.

195
00:19:43,561 --> 00:19:46,606
We are nothing. You have all the power.

196
00:20:11,798 --> 00:20:13,967
What if I freed your friends?

197
00:20:14,092 --> 00:20:17,137
Would you promise to stay?
Commit to serving me?

198
00:20:19,180 --> 00:20:24,644
If a Jedi as noble as you gave his word,
I think you might keep it.

199
00:20:25,353 --> 00:20:27,480
I don't trust you.

200
00:20:27,522 --> 00:20:32,986
Have I been anything but honest?
I have no reason to lie. I am who I am.

201
00:20:33,027 --> 00:20:36,030
It is you, you, who are the complicated one.

202
00:20:36,823 --> 00:20:42,203
Now, Master Skywalker, the future
of your friends lays in your hands.

203
00:20:42,328 --> 00:20:47,000
If they are to live as slaves,
it will be you who keeps them that way.

204
00:20:47,024 --> 00:20:52,024
http://hiqve.com/

